<paragraph blockId="10.[132,681,1304,1872]" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis box="[132,360,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">
Discussão: 
<taxonomicName authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[245,360,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geminus" status="sp. nov.">A. geminus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[373,457,1304,1327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
pode ser facilmente confundido com 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerremans, 1903" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[310,592,1336,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis box="[310,406,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">A. eversor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KERREMANS, C." box="[412,592,1336,1360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" pagination="49 - 338" refId="ref15260" refString="KERREMANS, C. 1903. Coleoptera Serricornia, Fam. Buprestidae. In: P. Wytsman. (Ed.). Genera Insectorum. Bruxelles Verteneuil &amp; Desmet. Fasc. 12 b; 12 c; 12 d p. 49 - 338." type="journal article" year="1903">Kerremans, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, do qual é simpátrico. Todavia, a fronte de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[508,608,1368,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis box="[508,608,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">A. eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
é lisa, pouco sulcada e desprovida dos lobos arredondados. Dorsalmente difere pelo ápice elitral arredondado e microdenticulado, enquanto em 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[488,590,1464,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis box="[488,590,1464,1488]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">A. eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
o ápice possui sempre um dente proeminente pequeno. Ventralmente os urosternitos de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[433,530,1528,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis box="[433,530,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">A. eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possuem uma pubescência branca dos lados do segundo e a faixa mediana termina no primeiro, enquanto a processo prosternal tem lados paralelos. Em relação aos órgãos genitais, o lobo mediano do edeago de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[549,661,1656,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geminus">
<emphasis box="[549,661,1656,1680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="91">A. geminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
é mais acuminado.
</paragraph>
